{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599282","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599282"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15538"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15538","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15538"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8229"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102105"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8229","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8229"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15538"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84552"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6902"},{"type":"tags","id":"7010"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19898"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19901"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23632"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102105","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102105"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe suprarenal (adrenal) glands are paired endocrine organs located in the retroperitoneal space. Each gland has a distinctive shape and position relative to surrounding structures.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following correctly describes the shape and relative position of the suprarenal glands?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The right gland is pyramidal and the left is crescentic; the right is positioned inferior to the left.","The right gland is crescentic and the left is pyramidal; the right is positioned superior to the left.","The right gland is pyramidal and the left is crescentic; the right is positioned superior to the left.","The right gland is crescentic and the left is pyramidal; the right is positioned inferior to the left.","The right gland is triangular and the left is triangular; both are positioned at the same level."],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct anatomical description is that \u003Cstrong\u003Ethe right gland is pyramidal and the left is crescentic; the right is positioned inferior to the left\u003C/strong\u003E. The right suprarenal gland has a pyramidal shape and sits in a more inferior position compared to the left suprarenal gland. The left suprarenal gland has a crescentic shape and sits in a more superior position compared to the right.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe right gland is crescentic and the left is pyramidal; the right is positioned superior to the left\u003C/strong\u003E - This completely reverses the correct anatomy of both glands in terms of both shape and position.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe right gland is pyramidal and the left is crescentic; the right is positioned superior to the left\u003C/strong\u003E - This correctly identifies the shapes but incorrectly describes their relative positions.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe right gland is crescentic and the left is pyramidal; the right is positioned inferior to the left\u003C/strong\u003E - This incorrectly describes the shapes of both glands while correctly describing their relative positions.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe right gland is triangular and the left is triangular; both are positioned at the same level\u003C/strong\u003E - This incorrectly states that both glands have the same shape and are at the same level.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe right suprarenal gland sits more inferiorly because the liver pushes the right kidney downward. The left suprarenal gland sits more superiorly because the left kidney is positioned higher than the right kidney. These anatomical relationships are important for surgical approaches and radiological interpretation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The right suprarenal gland is pyramidal in shape while the left suprarenal gland is crescentic.","The right suprarenal gland is situated more inferiorly than the left suprarenal gland.","Understanding the shape and position of the suprarenal glands is important for anatomical identification and surgical approaches."],"references":["Lotfi CFP, Kremer JL, Dos Santos Passaia B, Cavalcante IP. The human adrenal cortex: growth control and disorders. Clinics (Sao Paulo). 2018 Sep 6;73(suppl 1):e473s. doi: 10.6061/clinics/2018/e473s. PMID: 30208164; PMCID: PMC6113920","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84552"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15538"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84552","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/84552"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-07T18:09:14+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-07T18:12:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8229"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102105"}}},"meta":{"can